### [40] Create origin story (artisan)
POST {{base}}/origin-stories
Authorization: Bearer {{artisanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "product": "{{productId}}",
  "origin": {
    "region": "Amman",
    "village": "Jabal Al-Weibdeh",
    "coordinates": { "lat": 31.9566, "lng": 35.9239 }
  },
  "craftingProcess": "The leather is first soaked in a natural tannin bath for 48 hours to achieve the vegetable-tan finish. It is then hand-cut using steel templates, saddle-stitched with waxed linen thread, and burnished along the edges using a bone folder. Final conditioning is done with natural beeswax. The entire process takes approximately two full days of work per wallet.",
  "materialsSource": "Leather is sourced from a family-run tannery in Zarqa that has operated for over 60 years. Linen thread and hardware are imported from Italy to ensure quality.",
  "culturalSignificance": "Leatherwork has deep roots in Jordanian Bedouin culture, where saddles, bags, and sheaths were essential daily items. This wallet carries that tradition forward in a modern, everyday form.",
  "artisanPersonalNote": "I learned to cut leather from my uncle who made traditional saddles. Now I bring that same precision to wallets and bags for everyday use.",
  "estimatedCraftingTime": "2 full days per unit",
  "generationsTaught": "Learned from uncle, second generation in the family craft."
}

###

### [41] Update origin story (artisan/admin)
PUT {{base}}/origin-stories/{{originStoryId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{artisanToken}}
